Description:
EXPLORE YOUR OPTIONS - CENTRAL DANDENONG!
Situated in a very sought after location youll find this fantastic opportunity to reside in a wonderful old family home in one of Central Dandenongs best streets.
With charming street appeal and spacious living, the accommodation offers a lounge with brick open fire place, large adjoining dining area, three bedrooms with the huge main offering a full wall sliding door robes and a full ensuite. The second bedroom is large with a walk-in robe and the third bedroom has built in robes. The kitchen is spacious with plenty of cupboards, bench space and two pantries. Theres an adjoining family area overlooking the massive back yard, family bathroom and large laundry with adjoining toilet and storage cupboard.
Other features enhancing the home are hardwood polished floorboards, art deco ceilings in the lounge, dining and main bedroom, very high ceilings, decorative cornice, ducted heating and ducted vacuum.
Outside you have a double garage, large shed in the rear garden and plenty of space for off street parking.
Set on a huge block of 980m2 approx - in the Residential Growth Zone Schedule 1 (RGZ1), the new owner has the option to consider re-development with townhouses, apartments or just two substantial house and land packages, all STCA of course.
CLOSE TO THE PLAZA, MARKET, STATION & SCHOOLS!

Description:
A CLASSIC LOW MAINTENANCE HOME NEAR CENTRAL DANDENONG
Set on an allotment of approximately 372sqm, this home offers opportunities for home buyers and investors alike. Easy care nature and handy location just minutes from all of Dandenong's great facilities including shops, market, buses and multicultural eateries. With its brick and steel front fence, mottled cream brick facade and side carport/covered patio area, it has a welcoming presence from the street and inside you find high ceilings, picture rails and many other classic design cues. Features include a generous lounge room with a split system heater/air conditioner complemented by a neat kitchen with upright oven/stove and an included meals area. There are 3 bedrooms including 2 with built in wardrobes as well as a bathroom with the added luxury of a spa bath. Outside there is a great front yard that the kids can play in behind gates while requiring only minimal maintenance. All this and much more with the added bonus of no owners' corporation.

In a great position opposite the Dandenong Aquatic Centre, this classic brick veneer home
on around 614sqm has plenty of potential options for its new owner. You could easily renovate

Description:
STOP RENTING. START OWNING.
Why rent when you can buy? This splendid two-bedroom apartment ticks all the boxes for affordable and convenient living in a central location. Both bedrooms are well proportioned with built in robes and quiet carpet underfoot while the main living area offers plenty of space and the comfort of split system air conditioning. The practical kitchen includes a gas cooktop, wall oven and meals area with tiled floor and light coloured cabinetry contributing an airy feel. There's ceiling fans in the main living area and one of the bedrooms with the central bathroom incorporating laundry facilities. Imagine how convenient life will be when you're living a short walk from the myriad of shops at nearby Dandenong Plaza. Dandenong railway station is also close by as are a range of green parks and recreation areas. If you're looking to break the rent cycle or add to an investment portfolio this exciting apartment should be at the top of your list to inspect. Call now!

Description:
An Outstanding Townhouse in Sought After Location
This well-kept townhouse is ideally located a stone’s throw from everything that central Dandenong has to offer including Hospital, Chisholm TAFE, Market, Plaza and High School. Sitting quietly and independently at the rear of the development, the property offers 3 bedrooms, with 1 bedroom being located on the ground floor, formal lounge area, separate kitchen, meals and family area, central bathroom with separate toilet, additional ground floor powder room and possibility to convert laundry/powder room into full ground floor bathroom. Additionally, the well-built and modern home offers central gas ducted heating, split system air conditioning, floating timber floors and carpets through living areas and bedrooms, loads of natural light through the entire home, and ample storage space throughout. Externally, this home provides an abundance of space with a very generously sized backyard with dual patios, small balcony off bedroom overlooking the court, single lock up garage with possibility to park additional car off street in front of the garage, and much, much more. With an existing tenant in place currently paying $1499 per calendar month and on a month to month agreement, this property is perfect for first home buyers, small families, investors or people looking to downsize. Make sure that you view this home before it is too late!
Contact: Neb Delibasic on 0411 332 467
Auction: Saturday 5th August 2017 at 11:30am, On Site
Terms: 10% Deposit, Balance in 30-90 Days
